hopobject.body: What do you study? weight loss with pcos Some friends were supportive, reassuring her that they knew she would prevail. Others were quick to join the chorus of negative comments. Her siblings weren't shocked – they "assumed" this would happen, after all, and Rodriguez heard "told you so" more than a few times. Her boyfriend's parents were among the most disheartened: "They were furious, and they didn't talk to him for a while," she says. "They told us we had ruined our lives, and that now we had to stick together and worry about the baby."
